{"issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/5329", "repo": "rails", "body": "I honestly did not care that my change was rejected (the patch in our app was obviously `!!request.xhr?`).\r\n\r\nThere are two things troubling to me here:\r\n\r\n- @tpope's patch was reverted (which was nice, performant, and kept compatibility with Rails 2.3)\r\n- #5572 was closed by @fxn \r\n\r\nIt's obvious there was no contract to return a singleton here. You're just screwing over people using a debugger by making them jump through a mental hoop and breaking compatibility for the sake of change.\r\n\r\nI'll go back to work now. There are more important things to do.", "_id": {"$oid": "523819bdbd3543c15100e252"}, "issue_id": 5329, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/4725549", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/5329#issuecomment-4725549", "updated_at": "2012-03-27T20:24:55Z", "user": {"subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/clifton/subscriptions", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/clifton/events{/privacy}", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/clifton/repos", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/clifton/gists{/gist_id}", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/clifton", "login": "clifton", "gravatar_id": "4cede21ea96795d2de831e9981cc81cd", "html_url": "https://github.com/clifton", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/clifton/following{/other_user}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/clifton/received_events", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/clifton/orgs", "avatar_url": "https://1.gravatar.com/avatar/4cede21ea96795d2de831e9981cc81cd?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2Fc27181a18d3b30d14d66a1a56c068548.png", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/clifton/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "id": 14217, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/clifton/followers", "type": "User"}, "created_at": "2012-03-27T20:24:55Z", "id": 4725549, "owner": "rails"}
